# Tailwind CSS Plugins

Plugins extend Tailwind with new utilities, components, base styles, and variants. v4 reduces the need for JS plugins by providing CSS-native extension points.

## Official Plugins

### @tailwindcss/typography

Adds `prose` classes for beautiful typographic defaults on rendered HTML (markdown, CMS content, API responses).

```bash
npm install @tailwindcss/typography
```

#### v4 (CSS)
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@plugin "@tailwindcss/typography";
```

#### v3 (JS config)
```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  plugins: [require("@tailwindcss/typography")],
};
```

#### Usage
```html
<article class="prose lg:prose-xl dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
  <h1>Article Title</h1>
  <p>This paragraph gets beautiful default styling.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>List items are properly styled</li>
    <li>With correct spacing and bullets</li>
  </ul>
  <pre><code>Code blocks too</code></pre>
</article>
```

Key prose modifiers: `prose-sm`, `prose-base`, `prose-lg`, `prose-xl`, `prose-2xl`, `prose-invert` (dark mode), `prose-gray`, `prose-zinc`, `prose-slate`.

Override specific elements: `prose-headings:text-blue-600`, `prose-a:text-indigo-500`, `prose-code:text-pink-500`, `prose-img:rounded-xl`.

### @tailwindcss/forms

Provides a form reset that makes form elements easy to style with utilities.

```bash
npm install @tailwindcss/forms
```

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@plugin "@tailwindcss/forms";
```

```html
<input type="text" class="rounded-md border-gray-300 shadow-sm focus:border-indigo-500 focus:ring-indigo-500" />
<select class="rounded-md border-gray-300 shadow-sm focus:border-indigo-500 focus:ring-indigo-500">
  <option>Option 1</option>
</select>
<textarea class="rounded-md border-gray-300 shadow-sm focus:border-indigo-500 focus:ring-indigo-500"></textarea>
```

### @tailwindcss/container-queries (v3 only)

In v3, container queries required this plugin. In v4, container queries are built-in — see [[tailwind/responsive#container-queries]].

```bash
# v3 only
npm install @tailwindcss/container-queries
```

## v4 CSS-Native Extensions

v4 replaces many plugin use cases with CSS directives.

### Custom Utilities (@utility)

Create utilities that work with all variants (hover, responsive, dark):

```css
@utility content-auto {
  content-visibility: auto;
}

@utility scrollbar-hidden {
  &::-webkit-scrollbar {
    display: none;
  }
}
```

Usage: `content-auto`, `hover:content-auto`, `md:content-auto`

### Functional Utilities with Values

```css
@utility tab-* {
  tab-size: --value(--tab-size-*);
}
```

Usage: `tab-4`, `tab-8` (requires corresponding theme values)

### Custom Variants (@custom-variant)

```css
@custom-variant theme-midnight (&:where([data-theme="midnight"] *));
```

Usage: `theme-midnight:bg-black`, `theme-midnight:text-white`

### Custom Component Classes (@layer components)

```css
@layer components {
  .btn-primary {
    border-radius: calc(infinity * 1px);
    background-color: var(--color-violet-500);
    padding-inline: --spacing(5);
    padding-block: --spacing(2);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    color: var(--color-white);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }
}
```

## v3 Plugin API (Legacy)

For complex plugins that need JavaScript logic:

```javascript
const plugin = require("tailwindcss/plugin");

module.exports = plugin(function ({ addUtilities, addComponents, addBase, addVariant, matchUtilities, theme }) {
  // Add simple utilities
  addUtilities({
    ".content-auto": { "content-visibility": "auto" },
    ".content-hidden": { "content-visibility": "hidden" },
  });

  // Add components
  addComponents({
    ".card": {
      backgroundColor: theme("colors.white"),
      borderRadius: theme("borderRadius.lg"),
      padding: theme("spacing.6"),
      boxShadow: theme("boxShadow.xl"),
    },
  });

  // Add base styles
  addBase({
    "h1": { fontSize: theme("fontSize.2xl") },
    "h2": { fontSize: theme("fontSize.xl") },
  });

  // Add custom variant
  addVariant("optional", "&:optional");
  addVariant("hocus", ["&:hover", "&:focus"]);

  // Dynamic utilities from theme values
  matchUtilities(
    { "tab": (value) => ({ tabSize: value }) },
    { values: theme("tabSize") }
  );
});
```

## Loading JS Plugins in v4

Use the `@plugin` directive:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@plugin "@tailwindcss/typography";
@plugin "./my-custom-plugin.js";
```

## When to Use What

| Need | v4 Approach | v3 Approach |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| Custom utility | `@utility` in CSS | `addUtilities()` in plugin |
| Custom variant | `@custom-variant` in CSS | `addVariant()` in plugin |
| Design tokens | `@theme` in CSS | `theme.extend` in config |
| Component class | `@layer components` | `addComponents()` in plugin |
| Complex JS logic | `@plugin "./file.js"` | `require()` in config |
| Typography | `@plugin "@tailwindcss/typography"` | `require()` in config |
| Form reset | `@plugin "@tailwindcss/forms"` | `require()` in config |
